   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LESSON TWO THE LORD'S TABLE MEETING 1 Scripture Reading: 1 Cor 11:17-34 OUTLINE</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Two categories of meetings:</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The ministry meetings: To preach the gospel Acts 2:6, 14.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>To give a report of God's work Acts 14:26-27.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>To read the apostles' writing the Scripture Acts 15:30-31.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The church meetings: The Lord's table meeting: On the first day of the week the Lord's Day Acts 20:6b-7a; 1 Cor 16:2.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>To partake of the Lord's table 1 Cor 10:21b.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>To eat the Lord's supper 1 Cor 11:20.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>To remember the Lord: The focus of the Lord's table: 1 All hymns, praises, thanks, testimonies, and words should be concentrated on the Lord Himself.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>2 All distractions should be avoided.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>By breaking the bread to apprehend with appreciation and thanks the Lord's physical body being broken for us Luke 22:19; 1 Cor 11:24.</S>
   </TEXT>
